Q: Regarding the derivatives folder: does the preprocessed fMRI and EEG data
   follow the same preprocessing pipeline described in your original publication
   (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jneumeth.2018.09.019), or have newer preprocessing
   methods been applied in this updated release (v1.0.2, 2024-08-07)? 
A: The FMRI data in the derivatives directory are already preprocessed. See
   Picchioni 2022 Neuroimage for details on the preprocessing. The files have
   all the preprocessing described there up to and including RETROICOR. The same
   applies to the EEG data. The gac and cbc files have the gradient artifact
   correct and cardioballistic correction already applied. See Moehlman 2019
   J Neurosci Methods for the details. 
